data.title: Troup County, Georgia Population 2024
data.text:
Troup County, Georgia 's estimated 2024 population is 71,237 with a growth rate of 0.7% in the past year according to the most recent United States census data. Troup County, Georgia is the 35th largest county in Georgia. The 2010 population was 67,060 and has seen a growth of 6.23% since that time.

The highest rate of high school graduation is among native american people with a rate of 100% .

The highest rate of bachelors degrees is among native american people with a rate of 63.16% .
